==English==
===Etymology===
From Latin '''aquarius''', ''"water carrier"'', from '''[[aqua]]''', ''water'', + adjective suffix '''[[-arius]]'''

===Proper noun===
'''Aquarius'''

# A [[constellation]] of stars supposedly shaped like a water carrier.
# The [[Zodiac]] sign for the water carrier, covering January 20 through February 18.

